                        "content": "The nurse is working at a Veterans Affairs clinic that provides services for homeless veterans. Which client would the nurse attend to first?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nMental health is common among veterans. Post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD) is one of the most prevalent problems and can easily lead to suicide, which occurs commonly in this population. A client with a plan to harm themself or others is a safety risk and need to be addressed first. Options 1 and 3 may or may not compete for priority, depending on other presenting factors. An infected wound can lead to a life-threatening situation, but the client with a persistent cough may have tuberculosis and this is a communicable disease. The client with a history of substance abuse can be attended to last.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nNote the strategic word, first. From the options provided, you must select what client finding must be addressed before the others. The client with a plan to harm themself poses an immediate safety risk to themself and others. This client, therefore, must be attended to first.",
